    <item>
      <title>ML for Blockchain Compliance: Real-World Challenges</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1314/blog/blockchain-ml-compliance/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 15 Jan 2025 10:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1314/blog/blockchain-ml-compliance/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Building ML systems for blockchain compliance presents unique challenges that traditional fintech doesn&amp;rsquo;t face. Here&amp;rsquo;s what I&amp;rsquo;ve learned monitoring $30B+ in assets at Range.org.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;the-blockchain-data-challenge&#34;&gt;The Blockchain Data Challenge&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Unlike traditional financial data, blockchain transactions are:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Immutable&lt;/strong&gt; but &lt;strong&gt;pseudonymous&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Real-time&lt;/strong&gt; at massive scale&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-chain&lt;/strong&gt; across 21+ networks&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Complex&lt;/strong&gt; with smart contract interactions&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;key-use-cases-weve-solved&#34;&gt;Key Use Cases We&amp;rsquo;ve Solved&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;1-stablecoin-compliance-monitoring&#34;&gt;1. Stablecoin Compliance Monitoring&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Challenge&lt;/strong&gt;: Track USDC transfers across chains for KYT/AML compliance.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Solution&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Production LLM Systems: Key Lessons</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1314/blog/building-production-llm-systems/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 15 Dec 2024 10:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1314/blog/building-production-llm-systems/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Two years building production LLM systems taught me that &lt;strong&gt;research prototypes ≠ production systems&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;the-reality-check&#34;&gt;The Reality Check&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Our customer vulnerability prediction system started with GPT-4 for everything. Great demos, terrible production:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Too slow (5+ seconds)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Too expensive (£100+ per 1000 requests)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Unreliable at scale&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;what-actually-works&#34;&gt;What Actually Works&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;1-hybrid-architecture&#34;&gt;1. Hybrid Architecture&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;Input → Fast Classifier → [High Confidence] → Response&#xA;           ↓&#xA;      [Uncertain] → LLM → Human Review → Response&#xA;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Result&lt;/strong&gt;: 80% handled by fast models, 10x cost reduction.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Adding Images to Your Hugo Portfolio</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1314/blog/adding-images-hugo/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 15 Dec 2024 10:00:00 +0600</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1314/blog/adding-images-hugo/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;adding-images-to-your-hugo-portfolio&#34;&gt;Adding Images to Your Hugo Portfolio&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Images make your portfolio and blog posts much more engaging and professional. Here&amp;rsquo;s how you can add them to both your blog posts and portfolio projects.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;blog-post-images&#34;&gt;Blog Post Images&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;method-1-featured-image-in-frontmatter&#34;&gt;Method 1: Featured Image in Frontmatter&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Add an &lt;code&gt;image&lt;/code&gt; field to your blog post&amp;rsquo;s frontmatter:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div style=&#34;color:#4d4d4d;background-color:#fff;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;table style=&#34;border-spacing:0;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style=&#34;vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#4d4d4d;background-color:#fff;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f&#34;&gt;1&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f&#34;&gt;2&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f&#34;&gt;3&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f&#34;&gt;4&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;&lt;td style=&#34;vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;;width:100%&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#4d4d4d;background-color:#fff;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-yaml&#34; data-lang=&#34;yaml&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;---&lt;span style=&#34;color:#cbcbcb&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#cbcbcb&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#2c5dcd;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;title&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;span style=&#34;color:#cbcbcb&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0c6&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Your Blog Post Title&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#cbcbcb&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#cbcbcb&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#2c5dcd;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;image&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;span style=&#34;color:#cbcbcb&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0c6&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;/images/blog/your-image.jpg&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#cbcbcb&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#cbcbcb&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;---&lt;span style=&#34;color:#cbcbcb&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;method-2-images-in-content&#34;&gt;Method 2: Images in Content&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;You can also add images directly in your markdown content:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
