    <item>
      <title>Building Blockchain Security at Scale</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1314/blog/first-blog/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 01 Aug 2024 12:14:34 +0600</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1314/blog/first-blog/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;After years building AI systems for healthcare and LLMs, I&amp;rsquo;ve found my most challenging and impactful work yet: &lt;strong&gt;blockchain security and compliance at Range.org&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;the-transition-to-blockchain&#34;&gt;The Transition to Blockchain&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Moving from traditional ML to blockchain required learning entirely new paradigms:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Healthcare AI&lt;/strong&gt;: Structured data, regulated environments, batch processing&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Blockchain ML&lt;/strong&gt;: Graph data, pseudonymous actors, real-time requirements&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The shift wasn&amp;rsquo;t just technical—it was philosophical. In blockchain, &lt;strong&gt;trust is code&lt;/strong&gt;, and every system must be designed for adversarial environments.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
